description:
Now, we follow John Knox and his journey into becoming Scotland's greatest reformer. John Knox started his ministry as a two-handed sword carrier to protect George Wishart. But, after Wisharts unfortunate death, Knox picked up the mantle. He spent time in England and Switzerland, but came back to Scotland, where he drove the Scottish Reformation forward through his boldness, fearlessness and resolute trust in God.

To find out more about John Knox visit our website to read our extended article.
